  "description": "Codex CLI usage analytics on Prometheus: turns, token volume by type/model, turn and MCP tool latency. Consumes Codex's own OpenTelemetry [otel] metrics export via a dedicated otelcol receiver (skel/etc/otelcol.yaml.tmpl's otlp/codex). Dashboard/fleet visibility only — Codex has no direct cost metric and this dashboard never computes one; WMS cost attribution is fed exclusively by the codex-scraper JSONL tailer, never by OTEL (see research/otel-v1.md in teamster-codex-kit). Requires Grafana 11+.",
  "editable": false,
  "fiscalYearStartMonth": 0,
  "graphTooltip": 1,
  "panels": [
    {
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 3,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "code": {
          "language": "markdown",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "**Scope:** dashboard/fleet metrics only, fed by Codex's own `[otel]` export — WMS work-unit attribution and token **cost** come exclusively from the `codex-scraper` JSONL tailer (never from OTEL; Codex has no cost metric of its own, only token counts). Codex's metrics are delta temporality; `deltatocumulative` (otelcol-contrib ≥0.120.0) converts them to cumulative ahead of `prometheus_remote_write` — confirmed end-to-end with real `codex exec` traffic (see `research/evidence-round3/` in the teamster-codex-kit for both the original live capture and the otelcol-temporality-bump verification).",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "12.1.1",
      "title": "",
      "transparent": true,
      "type": "text"
    },
